# ISS-562 - scripted test for the sge-build BROWSER packaging task.
# Exercises SgePackaging.sgePackageBrowser (browser HTML generation + main.js
# copy) and the multiarch-resources embedded-resources sourceGenerator against a
# fresh hello-world project built on the locally-published sge-build plugin. The
# fullLinkJS step is bypassed by overriding sgeJsOutputDir to a stub directory
# containing a fake main.js (see build.sbt) — so the real HTML/copy logic runs
# without invoking the Scala.js linker.

# Assert the package contents via the custom checkBrowserPackage task. This task
# compiles the JS axis (running the embedded-resources sourceGenerator) and runs
# game.js(...) / sgePackageBrowser, then asserts (against the actual task outputs,
# so it is robust to the projectMatrix target layout):
#   - index.html exists + contains the title, the <script src="main.js"> tag,
#     and the Loading/app-name text
#   - main.js was copied into the output
#   - the generated, self-registering GeneratedEmbeddedResources.scala object is
#     produced and registers the expected resource paths
#   - CANARY: assets/assets.txt (and the assets/ dir) are ABSENT
> checkBrowserPackage
